  <summary>&lt;h2>Wallpaper Engine for Plasma 6 (types: video, web &amp;amp; &lt;em>scene via seperate plugin-lib&lt;/em>)&lt;/h2>

&lt;ol>
&lt;li>get Wallpaper Engine (installed on Steam)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Subscribe to wallpapers (Steam Workshop)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Select &amp;gt;steamlibrary folder&amp;lt; containing 'steamapps' where WE is installed:&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;p>Default Steam library path on Linux: ~/.local/share/Steam
Default Steam library path on Steam-Deck: /home/deck/.steam/steam
(&amp;gt;&amp;gt; not found? try 'show hidden files' and / or copy / paste path in file chooser)&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
&lt;li>if some wallpapers dont run ('plugin-lib not found'):&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;ol>
&lt;li>install extra plugin-lib via QT6-package (deb, arch, steamdeck; precompiled): https://github.com/slynobody/SteamOS-wallpaper-engine-kde-plugin
or&lt;/li>
&lt;li>compile extra plugin-lib yourself: https://github.com/catsout/wallpaper-engine-kde-plugin&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;ul>
&lt;li>if some wallpapers have errors:&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;ol>
&lt;li>downgrade WE 'to previous' in steam (app, properties, "beta")&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;ul>
&lt;li>If a wallpaper crash your Desktop / Plasma
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Remove WallpaperFilePath line in ~/.config/plasma-org.kde.plasma.desktop-appletsrc and restart KDE to fix.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;hr />

